Ft Dance Floor ** Balcony DJ MANCUB - SPACE COWBOYS Chip Corwin, (a.k.a.) DJ Mancub, is one of San Francisco's premiere DJ’s. Mancub delivers a one-two punch, some times using authentic boxing gloves during his performance. He is the only DJ in San Francisco to use such a peculiar technique. Expect a T.K.O.! He represents the world famous Space Cowboys and Sleevin Records in San Francisco. For the last 4 years he as been voted into the top eleven dj's of San Francisco along with Mark Farina, Miguel Miggs, Bassnectar, Fred Everything, Smoove, M3 and David Harness. . Aileen Lawlor - Poi Class Aileen has quickly established herself in the international spinning community as a dynamic dancer, displaying not only technical proficiency with her poi and staff skills, but a unique and graceful style that integrates her experience with yoga, dance, and gymnastics. Aileen has appeared in instructional DVDs for both Contact Staff and Poi Technique, as well as the 2009 Circles of Light DVD. She has performed throughout the world and teaches group classes at the Flowspace and private classes out of her home at the Vulcan warehouse, which has become known worldwide as a hotbed for talent and innovation in the spinning and juggling arts. http://www.youtube.com/user/aileenbean FlowToys Flowtoys is a San Francisco Bay Area-based company that produces high performance glow poi, staff and other light up toys for dance, martial arts, entertainment and fun. Flowtoys also provides a viable healthy complement and alternative to firedancing. Find your flow in the endless possibilities of these tools for creative expression and exploration of movement. www.flowtoys.com

Wiser Together: Collaborating Across Generations
Dustin Moskovitz was invited
These are times that are calling the generations to come together. Join Generation Waking Up, Thrive Bay Area, Impact Hub Oakland, and community partners for a special event called "Wiser Together - Collaborating Across Generations." This will be the first event in a series of intergenerational convenings bringing together youth, adults, and elders from around Oakland and the Bay Area. The purpose of this series is to build community connections across generations, to unleash innovative solutions, and to support intergenerational collaboration around local community projects. During this first event, we will use the World Café conversation methodology to explore the questions: What are the gifts we each bring as a generation? What are effective approaches for intergenerational collaboration? What is our vision for the future of our communities and how can we work together to make it happen? Live music and performing artists will kick the night off. Snacks and beverages will also be provided. Tickets are a sliding scale of $10-20, and no one will be turned away for lack of funds. People of all ages ready to engage in community conversation are welcome. Bring a younger. Bring an elder. Bring your community! Please send any questions and inquires to hanni@generationwakingup.org. Co-Sponsors: Generation Waking Up is a nonprofit organization igniting young changemakers to bring forth a thriving, just, and sustainable world. Thrive Bay Area is a local initiative unleashing creativity and collaboration for more just, beautiful, and resilient communities. Impact Hub Oakland is an inspiring working space, entrepreneurial incubator, and membership-based community of social engaged people pioneering solutions for a sustainable and equitable world. The World Cafe Community Foundation (www.worldcafe.org) is nonprofit organization transforming the world for the benefit of all life through convening and supporting collaborative conversations globally.

Concept 01: Life and Death, by Mattie Bowen
Dustin Moskovitz was invited
– – OUR DEBUT EVENT – – Concept SF presents... CONCEPT 01: LIFE AND DEATH "Life as I understand it. And Death as I imagine it to be." by Mattie Bowen (aka Mossmoss | As You Like It ) with support from Alex Blackstock (Concept | Less Is More) $5 at the door \\\\\\ • Free tasty snacks to be provided from 6:30-8:15pm • Specialty concept-inspired cocktail by Alex Blackstock • Pristine Turbosound System from 222 Hyde \\\\\\ ABOUT CONCEPT www.concept-sf.com Concept is an experiment in musical communication, via the art of the dj. Concept offers accomplished local artists the opportunity to select a theme or idea - a concept - to interpret through music. The artist maintains complete control over the selection of the concept, and its interpretation. He or she then presents that interpretation in a live performance at Mercer Nightclub & Lounge in San Francisco. Please note that this is not a dance music event. Though featured artists may include dance music of various forms in their performance, doing so is not required or expected. Finally, at Concept we believe that to facilitate communication, the audience must have the opportunity to engage comfortably with the artists' creative expression. So our listening environment supports the musical experience. \\\\\\ ABOUT MATTIE BOWEN https://soundcloud.com/mossmoss http://www.residentadvisor.net/dj/mossmoss Mattie Bowen is a Scottish born dj and producer. With a keen ear and eye for detail, he is an artist by nature. His wandering sets paint landscapes of light and dark patterns, textures, and strange melody. Mattie's inspiration draws from the organic details of existence, the tiny pieces most overlook in exchange for the big-picture rush of an ever changing modern world. His mind is set deeply to explore these facets and to share his exploration in all forms to those that might look and listen. Mossmoss currently resides San Francisco and draws on The City and its colorful nightlife for constant immersive inspiration. \\\\\\ ABOUT MERCER www.mercer-sf.com Liquore lounge, gallery, and art space located in the Design District - San Francisco
